{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1619,"text":"Ten years ago,"},{"time":3089,"text":"I got a phone call that\nchanged my life."},{"time":6897,"text":"At the time, I was \ncardiologist at UCLA,"},{"time":10849,"text":"specializing in cardiac \nimaging techniques."},{"time":14286,"text":"The call came from a veterinarian\nat the Los Angeles Zoo."},{"time":19815,"text":"An elderly female chimpanzee"},{"time":22469,"text":"had woken up with a facial droop"},{"time":25292,"text":"and the veterinarians were worried\nthat she'd had a stroke."},{"time":28628,"text":"They asked if I'd \ncome to the zoo"},{"time":31653,"text":"and image the animal's heart"},{"time":33601,"text":"to look for a possible\ncardiac cause."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37291,"text":"Now, to be clear, North American\nzoos are staffed"},{"time":40929,"text":"by highly qualified, \nboard-certified veterinarians"},{"time":45058,"text":"who take outstanding \ncare of their animal patients."},{"time":49727,"text":"But occasionally, they do reach into \nthe human medical community,"},{"time":53813,"text":"particularly for some \nspeciality consultation,"},{"time":58414,"text":"and I was one of the lucky physicians\nwho was invited in to help."},{"time":64233,"text":"I had a chance to rule out\na stroke in this chimpanzee"},{"time":70736,"text":"and make sure that this gorilla \ndidn't have a torn aorta,"},{"time":76800,"text":"evaluate this macaw\nfor a heart murmur,"},{"time":81587,"text":"make sure that this California sea lion's\nparicardium wasn't inflamed,"},{"time":89056,"text":"and in this picture, I'm listening\nto the heart of a lion"},{"time":93314,"text":"after a lifesaving, \ncollaborative procedure"},{"time":96931,"text":"with veterinarians and physicians"},{"time":99848,"text":"where we drained 700 cc's of \nfluid from the sac"},{"time":104165,"text":"in which this lion's \nheart was contained."},{"time":108569,"text":"And this procedure, which I have\ndone on many human patients,"},{"time":113382,"text":"was identical, with the exception\nof that paw and that tail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122733,"text":"Now most of the time, I was working\nat UCLA Medical Center with physicians,"},{"time":129124,"text":"discussing symptoms\nand diagnoses and treatments"},{"time":134158,"text":"for my human patients,"},{"time":137599,"text":"but some of the time,\nI was working at the Los Angeles Zoo"},{"time":140677,"text":"with veterinarians, discussing \nsymptoms and diagnoses and treatments"},{"time":146122,"text":"for their animal patients."},{"time":148748,"text":"And occasionally, on \nthe very same day,"},{"time":153841,"text":"I went on rounds at \nUCLA Medical Center"},{"time":157620,"text":"and at the Los Angeles Zoo."},{"time":160523,"text":"And here's what started coming\ninto very clear focus for me."},{"time":166861,"text":"Physicians and veterinarians\nwere essentially taking care"},{"time":171167,"text":"of the same disorders in their \nanimal and human patients:"},{"time":176337,"text":"congestive heart failure, brain tumors,"},{"time":180850,"text":"leukemia, diabetes, \narthritis, ALS, breast cancer,"},{"time":189101,"text":"even psychiatric syndromes\nlike depression, anxiety,"},{"time":194241,"text":"compulsions, eating disorders\nand self-injury."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200788,"text":"Now, I've got a confession to make."},{"time":203666,"text":"Even though I studied comparative\nphysiology and evolutionary biology"},{"time":210515,"text":"as an undergrad --"},{"time":212598,"text":"I had even written my senior \nthesis on Darwinian theory --"},{"time":217136,"text":"learning about the \nsignificant overlap"},{"time":219856,"text":"between the disorders of \nanimals and humans,"},{"time":222592,"text":"it came as a much needed \nwake-up call for me."},{"time":228311,"text":"So I started wondering,\nwith all of these overlaps,"},{"time":232799,"text":"how was it that I had never\nthought to ask a veterinarian,"},{"time":238317,"text":"or consult the veterinary literature,"},{"time":240844,"text":"for insights into one \nof my human patients?"},{"time":245173,"text":"Why had I never, nor had any of my \nphysician friends and colleagues"},{"time":251324,"text":"whom I asked, ever attended \na veterinary conference?"},{"time":258327,"text":"For that matter, why was \nany of this a surprise?"},{"time":264443,"text":"I mean, look, every single physician\naccepts some biological connection"},{"time":270588,"text":"between animals and humans."},{"time":273488,"text":"Every medication that we prescribe\nor that we've taken ourselves"},{"time":278257,"text":"or we've given to our families\n"},{"time":280891,"text":"has first been tested on an animal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284471,"text":"But there's something very different"},{"time":286227,"text":"about giving an animal a \nmedication or a human disease"},{"time":292832,"text":"and the animal developing \ncongestive heart failure"},{"time":296777,"text":"or diabetes or breast cancer \non their own."},{"time":303324,"text":"Now, maybe some of the surprise"},{"time":305955,"text":"comes from the increasing\nseparation in our world"},{"time":309539,"text":"between the urban and the nonurban."},{"time":313423,"text":"You know, we hear about these city kids"},{"time":316121,"text":"who think that wool grows on trees"},{"time":320192,"text":"or that cheese comes from a plant."},{"time":324256,"text":"Well, today's human hospitals,"},{"time":326989,"text":"increasingly, are turning into these\ngleaming cathedrals of technology."},{"time":333810,"text":"And this creates a psychological\ndistance between the human patients"},{"time":338717,"text":"who are being treated there"},{"time":341437,"text":"and animal patients who\nare living in oceans"},{"time":345934,"text":"and farms and jungles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349452,"text":"But I think there's an \neven deeper reason."},{"time":354561,"text":"Physicians and scientists, we accept\nintellectually that our species,"},{"time":361294,"text":"Homo sapiens, is merely \none species,"},{"time":365035,"text":"no more unique or\nspecial than any other."},{"time":370506,"text":"But in our hearts, we don't \ncompletely believe that."},{"time":376572,"text":"I feel it myself when I'm \nlistening to Mozart"},{"time":380866,"text":"or looking at pictures of the \nMars Rover on my MacBook."},{"time":386266,"text":"I feel that tug of \nhuman exceptionalism,"},{"time":391812,"text":"even as I recognize the \nscientifically isolating cost"},{"time":396370,"text":"of seeing ourselves as a\nsuperior species, apart."},{"time":402746,"text":"Well, I'm trying these days."},{"time":405979,"text":"When I see a human patient\nnow, I always ask,"},{"time":410441,"text":"what do the animal doctors know\nabout this problem that I don't know?"},{"time":415283,"text":"And, might I be taking better \ncare of my human patient"},{"time":420745,"text":"if I saw them as a human\nanimal patient?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427858,"text":"Here are a few examples of the \nkind of exciting connections\n"},{"time":432095,"text":"that this kind of \nthinking has led me to."},{"time":436057,"text":"Fear-induced heart failure."},{"time":438894,"text":"Around the year 2000,"},{"time":441398,"text":"human cardiologists \"discovered\"\nemotionally induced heart failure."},{"time":448898,"text":"It was described in a gambling father \nwho had lost his life's savings"},{"time":454000,"text":"with a roll of the dice,"},{"time":457152,"text":"in a bride who'd\nbeen left at the alter."},{"time":461823,"text":"But it turns out, this \n\"new\" human diagnosis"},{"time":466464,"text":"was neither new, nor\nwas it uniquely human."},{"time":470939,"text":"Veterinarians had been diagnosing, \ntreating and even preventing"},{"time":476867,"text":"emotionally induced\nsymptoms in animals"},{"time":480746,"text":"ranging from monkeys to flamingos,\nfrom to deer to rabbits,"},{"time":486650,"text":"since the 1970s."},{"time":490968,"text":"How many human lives \nmight have been saved"},{"time":494334,"text":"if this veterinary knowledge\nhad been put into the hands"},{"time":497939,"text":"of E.R. docs and cardiologists?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":503055,"text":"Self-injury."},{"time":505517,"text":"Some human patients \nharm themselves."},{"time":509652,"text":"Some pluck out patches of hair,"},{"time":513352,"text":"others actually cut themselves."},{"time":518242,"text":"Some animal patients \nalso harm themselves."},{"time":522064,"text":"There are birds that \npluck out feathers."},{"time":525544,"text":"There are stallions that repetitively\nbite their flanks until they bleed."},{"time":533313,"text":"But veterinarians have very specific\nand very effective ways"},{"time":538485,"text":"of treating and even\npreventing self-injury"},{"time":542904,"text":"in their self-injuring animals."},{"time":546686,"text":"Shouldn't this veterinary knowledge\nbe put into the hands"},{"time":549733,"text":"of psychotherapists and \nparents and patients"},{"time":553459,"text":"struggling with self-injury?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557497,"text":"Postpartum depression and \npostpartum psychosis."},{"time":562332,"text":"Sometimes, soon after giving birth,"},{"time":565467,"text":"some women become depressed,"},{"time":567891,"text":"and sometimes they become seriously \ndepressed and even psychotic."},{"time":572197,"text":"They may neglect their newborn,"},{"time":574761,"text":"and in some extreme cases,"},{"time":576937,"text":"even harm the child."},{"time":580086,"text":"Equine veterinarians also\nknow that occasionally,"},{"time":584312,"text":"a mare, soon after giving birth,"},{"time":587433,"text":"will neglect the foal,\nrefusing to nurse,"},{"time":590646,"text":"and in some instances,\nkick the foal, even to death."},{"time":597018,"text":"But veterinarians have devised"},{"time":599823,"text":"an intervention to deal with\nthis foal rejection syndrome"},{"time":605296,"text":"that involves increasing \noxytocin in the mare."},{"time":609561,"text":"Oxytocin is the bonding hormone,"},{"time":612946,"text":"and this leads to renewed interest,"},{"time":615635,"text":"on the part of the mare, in her foal."},{"time":619065,"text":"Shouldn't this information"},{"time":621121,"text":"be put into the hands of ob/gyn's"},{"time":624461,"text":"and family doctors and patients"},{"time":627794,"text":"who are struggling with postpartum\ndepression and psychosis?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":635306,"text":"Well, despite all of this promise,"},{"time":637653,"text":"unfortunately the gulf between\nour fields remains large."},{"time":645461,"text":"To explain it, I'm afraid I'm going \nto have to air some dirty laundry."},{"time":650990,"text":"Some physicians can be real snobs"},{"time":655095,"text":"about doctors who are not M.D.'s."},{"time":657649,"text":"I'm talking about dentists and \noptometrists and psychologists,"},{"time":663975,"text":"but maybe especially animal doctors."},{"time":668202,"text":"Of course, most physicians\ndon't realize that it is harder"},{"time":672075,"text":"to get into vet school these\ndays than medical school,"},{"time":676458,"text":"and that when we go \nto medical school,"},{"time":678742,"text":"we learn everything \nthere is to know"},{"time":681355,"text":"about one species, Homo sapiens,"},{"time":684478,"text":"but veterinarians need to learn\nabout health and disease"},{"time":688785,"text":"in mammals, amphibians,\nreptiles, fish and birds."},{"time":693763,"text":"So I don't blame the vets\nfor feeling annoyed"},{"time":698447,"text":"by my profession's\ncondescension and ignorance."},{"time":704412,"text":"But here's one from the vets:"},{"time":707152,"text":"What do you call a veterinarian"},{"time":710559,"text":"who can only take \ncare of one species?"},{"time":716416,"text":"A physician. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":719737,"text":"Closing the gap has become \na passion for me,"},{"time":725946,"text":"and I'm doing this \nthrough programs"},{"time":728547,"text":"like Darwin on Rounds at UCLA,"},{"time":731689,"text":"where we're bringing animal experts \nand evolutionary biologists"},{"time":737236,"text":"and embedding them\non our medical teams"},{"time":741388,"text":"with our interns and our residents."},{"time":745326,"text":"And through Zoobiquity conferences,"},{"time":749033,"text":"where we bring medical schools \ntogether with veterinary schools"},{"time":753252,"text":"for collabortive discussions"},{"time":755392,"text":"of the shared diseases and disorders\n"},{"time":758193,"text":"of animal and human patients."},{"time":762319,"text":"At Zoobiquity conferences,"},{"time":765162,"text":"participants learn how treating\nbreast cancer in a tiger"},{"time":770582,"text":"can help us better treat breast cancer"},{"time":773535,"text":"in a kindergarten teacher;"},{"time":776846,"text":"how understanding polycystic\noveries in a Holstein cow"},{"time":781709,"text":"can help us better take care"},{"time":783943,"text":"of a dance instructor \nwith painful periods;"},{"time":788503,"text":"and how better understanding the \ntreatment of separation anxiety"},{"time":793152,"text":"in a high-strung Sheltie"},{"time":795561,"text":"can help an anxious young child\nstruggling with his first days of school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802962,"text":"In the United States and now \ninternationally, at Zoobiquity conferences"},{"time":808207,"text":"physicians and veterinarians check \ntheir attitudes and their preconceptions"},{"time":815076,"text":"at the door and come \ntogether as colleagues,"},{"time":821100,"text":"as peers, as doctors."},{"time":826965,"text":"After all, we humans \nare animals, too,"},{"time":832385,"text":"and it's time for us physicians to embrace"},{"time":835845,"text":"our patients' and our own animal natures"},{"time":840392,"text":"and join veterinarians"},{"time":842530,"text":"in a species-spanning approach to health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847518,"text":"Because it turns out,"},{"time":849731,"text":"some of the best and \nmost humanistic medicine"},{"time":854929,"text":"is being practiced by doctors\nwhose patients aren't human."},{"time":860469,"text":"And one of the best ways \nwe can take care"},{"time":863851,"text":"of the human patient is by \npaying close attention"},{"time":868952,"text":"to how all the other \npatients on the planet"},{"time":872655,"text":"live, grow, get sick and heal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879312,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881897,"text":"(Applause)."}]}]}